<TITLE> BNP to hold 2-day programme on Ekushey </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 14 (bdnews24.com) Main opposition Bangladesh Nationaist Party announced a two-day programme beginning Feb 20 to mark the International Mother Language Day and Language Martyr's Day. The decision was taken at a meeting of the party at its Naya Palatan headquarters. BNP office secretary Rizvi Ahmed told reporters that a discussion meeting on language movement will be held on Fen 20 at the Diploma Engineers Institution auditorium in Dhaka. On Feb 21, the party leaders will place floral wreaths at the central Shaheed Minar, he said. In addition, BNP-backed cultural organisation Jatiyatabadi Samajik o Sangskritik Sangstha will arrange cultural programmes every evening from Feb 18 to Feb 20 at the premises adjacent to the graveyard of Ziaur Rahman, founder of BNP. Selima Rahman, Mirza Abbas and other standing committee members along with the leaders of other associate bodies were also present at the meeting. bdnew
